      <hedline>
        <hl1>That Pitch by Clemens</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Louise S Albenda letter disputes Jim Bouton's July 11 article on beaning of New York Mets catcher Pike Piazza by New York Yankees pitcher Roger Clemens during recent game; says Clemens should not go unpunished</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In regard to Roger Clemens's pitch at Mike Piazza's head (''Did He Throw It on Purpose?'', by Jim Bouton, Op-Ed, July 11):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In regard to Roger Clemens's pitch at Mike Piazza's head (''Did He Throw It on Purpose?'', by Jim Bouton, Op-Ed, July 11):</p>
        <p>A pitcher who chooses to throw an inside pitch, hits a batter and then claims to have lost control is negligent.</p>
        <p>A pitcher who intentionally throws a pitch to hit a batter is criminal. And a pitcher who fails to check on a fallen batter hit by his pitch is disgraceful.</p>
        <p>In either event, the pitcher's actions should not go unpunished.</p>
        <p>LOUISE S. ALBENDA  Brooklyn, July 12, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
